.TH SDL_GetRendererProperties 3 "SDL 3.0.0" "SDL" "SDL3 FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
SDL_GetRendererProperties \- Get the properties associated with a renderer\[char46]
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "SDL_PropertiesID SDL_GetRendererProperties(SDL_Renderer *renderer);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The following read-only properties are provided by SDL:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]renderer\[char46]d3d9\[char46]device" (pointer) - the IDirect3DDevice9 associated with the renderer
"SDL\[char46]renderer\[char46]d3d11\[char46]device" (pointer) - the ID3D11Device associated with the renderer
"SDL\[char46]renderer\[char46]d3d12\[char46]device" (pointer) - the ID3D12Device associated with the renderer
"SDL\[char46]renderer\[char46]d3d12\[char46]command_queue" (pointer) - the ID3D12CommandQueue associated with the renderer


.BR 

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I renderer
the rendering context
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns a valid property ID on success or 0 on failure; call

.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This function is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

